terms%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20Feigelson%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Mystro%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Uber%20has%20sent%20letters%20accusing%20his%20company%20of%20violating%20its%20terms%20of%20service%20and%20interfering%20with%20its%20relationships%20with%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20we're%20aligned%20with%20at%20least%20their%20publicly%20stated%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20Feigelson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20believes%20his%20app%20promotes%20driver%20safety%20by%20keeping%20drivers'%20eyes%20on%20the%20road.%20He%20said%20he%20hopes%20the%20companies%20can%20reach%20a%20deal.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20certainly%20are%20worried%2C%20especially%20with%20Uber's%20cease-and-desist%20letters%2C%20that%20they%20might%20sue%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Uber%20representative%20said%20they%20wouldn't%20talk%20about%20any%20specific%20app%2C%20but%20said%20%26quot%3Busing%20third-party%20tools%20to%20bypass%20the%20system%20breaks%20our%20Community%20Guidelines%20and%20Terms%20of%20Service.%20It%20hurts%20riders%2C%20other%20drivers%2C%20and%20the%20trust%20that%20keeps%20Uber%20running.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20apps%20often%20use%20an%20Android%20phone's%20accessibility%20features%20to%20read%20the%20screen%20and%20overlay%20a%20widget%20to%20guide%20the%20driver.%20Feigelson%20said%20Mystro%20uses%20ride%20and%20delivery%20apps'%20application%20programming%20interfaces%2C%20or%20APIs%2C%20so%20that%20drivers%20can%20automatically%20accept%20and%20reject%20offers%20based%20on%20criteria%20they%20select%2C%20such%20as%20the%20ride's%20per-mile%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20aren't%20free%2C%20but%20they%20say%20drivers%20can%20increase%20their%20earnings%20by%20more%20than%20what%20the%20tools%20cost%2C%20which%20ranges%20from%20%245%20to%20%2419%20a%20month.%20Some%20drivers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-drivers-make-fulltime-cancelling-rides-gig-economy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20can%20make%20more%20money%20if%20they're%20pickier%20about%20the%20rides%20they%20accept%2C%20though%20for%20Uber%20drivers%2C%20declining%20rides%20based%20on%20destinations%20can%20put%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Ftw%2Fen%2Fdeliver%2Fdelivery-platform%2Fdeactivation-review%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etheir%20accounts%20at%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20upon%20a%20time%2C%20Uber%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20technological%20disruptor%2C%20upsetting%20incumbent%20taxi%20companies%20and%20bucking%20outdated%20local%20rules%20on%20ride%20services.%20The%20company%20even%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2017%2F03%2F03%2Ftechnology%2Fuber-greyball-program-evade-authorities.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20project%20called%20Greyball%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20it%20used%20for%20years%20to%20serve%20up%20a%20fake%20version%20of%20the%20app%20to%20regulators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20it's%20the%20one%20cracking%20down.%20GigU%2C%20which%20launched%20in%20the%20United%20States%20in%20May%2C%20was%20sued%20by%20Uber%20in%20Brazil%2C%20where%20it%20says%20its%20app%20has%20been%20downloaded%20a%20half-million%20times.%20GigU%20says%20it%20has%20come%20out%20ahead%2C%20although%20Uber%20has%20said%20the%20legal%20process%20is%20ongoinGigUigU%20also%20said%20it%20has%20filed%20an%20antitrust%20complaint%20against%20Uber%20with%20CADE%2C%20a%20Brazilian%20regulator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20said%20its%20driver%20app%20is%20transparent%20about%20where%20demand%20is%20high%20and%20where%20a%20particular%20ride%20would%20go%20and%20how%20much%20a%20driver%20would%20make%20from%20it.%20Transferring%20credentials%20violates%20its%20terms%20of%20service%2C%20the%20representative%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUsing%20automation%20tools%2C%20apps%2C%20or%20bots%20to%20manipulate%20the%20Uber%20app%20or%20access%20Uber%20data%20in%20any%20way%20isn't%20allowed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuiz%20Gustavo%20Neves%2C%20GigU's%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%2C%20also%20told%20BI%20that%20some%20of%20its%20US%20users%20recently%20got%20an%20email%20from%20Lyft.%20The%20message%20told%20gig%20workers%20that%20Lyft%20had%20%26quot%3Bidentified%20unusual%20behavior%20associated%20with%20your%20driver%20account%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20third-party%20apps%2C%20of%20which%20GigU%20is%20one%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20not%20secure%20and%20not%20allowed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20message%20didn't%20specifically%20name%20GigU%20or%20any%20other%20apps%2C%20Lyft's%20message%20made%20the%20risks%20to%20drivers%20clear%3A%20%26quot%3BYour%20account%20may%20be%20at%20risk%20of%20deactivation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Lyft%20sent%20out%20the%20message%2C%20GigU%20and%20Mystro%20have%20both%20sought%20to%20argue%20that%20using%20the%20apps%20doesn't%20put%20drivers'%20access%20to%20Lyft%20at%20risk.%20GigU%20has%20published%20a%20blog%20post%20on%20its%20website%20and%20answered%20users'%20questions%20on%20Reddit%2C%20Neves%20said.%20GigU%20isn't%20violating%20Lyft's%20terms%20of%20service%2C%20Neves%20believes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Lyft%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20group%20isn't%20against%20all%20third-party%20apps%20and%20says%20it%20hasn't%20disabled%20any%20driver%20accounts%20for%20using%20them.%20It%20said%20that%20some%20of%20the%20apps%20cross%20lines%2C%20though%20it%20didn't%20name%20any.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnauthorized%20apps%20can%20harm%20the%20user%20experience%20and%20create%20an%20unfair%20marketplace%20for%20our%20drivers%2C%20for%20example%20by%20enabling%20automatic%20ride%20cancellations%2C%20delaying%20response%20times%2C%20and%20disadvantaging%20those%20who%20follow%20the%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20wrote%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20ride-hailing%20and%20delivery%20drivers%20still%20don't%20use%20third-party%20apps%20to%20screen%20their%20ride%20and%20delivery%20offers.%20The%20UberEatsDrivers%20forum%20on%20Reddit%2C%20which%20is%20run%20by%20drivers%20and%20has%2076%2C000%20members%2C%20says%20it%20will%20ban%20users%20who%20discuss%20what%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3Bcheating%20apps.%26quot%3B%20The%20rule%20singles%20out%20Para%2C%20which%20shut%20down%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Reddit%20posts%20by%20its%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMinsu%20Longiaru%2C%20an%20attorney%20with%20the%20worker%20advocacy%20group%20PowerSwitch%20Action%2C%20said%20it's%20unsurprising%20that%20ride-hailing%20drivers%20would%20turn%20to%20third-party%20apps%20in%20hopes%20of%20getting%20an%20edge.%20She%20said%20her%20group's%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.datocms-assets.com%2F64990%2F1751597557-ubers-inequality-machine.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20of%20Uber%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20most%20of%20them%20felt%20%26quot%3Bsqueezed%20and%20manipulated%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20app%20and%20said%20they%20often%20earned%20less%20than%20they%20expected%20because%20offers%20seemed%20to%20get%20worse%20as%20they%20approached%20their%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20that%20it's%20fair%20that%20drivers%20should%20be%20able%20to%20use%20tools%20that%20they%20have%20at%20their%20disposal%20to%20try%20and%20make%20a%20fair%20and%20decent%20wage%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20these%20third-party%20tools%20are%20not%20a%20substitute%20for%20real%20protection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20past%20fall%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D-tf4IiU91GU%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELyft%20executive%20Jeremy%20Byrd%20said%20%3C%2Fa%3Eit%20has%20made%20its%20app%20more%20transparent%20for%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20drivers%20and%20the%20teams%20behind%20the%20apps%20are%20skeptical%20of%20the%20gig%20apps'%20claims%20to%20be%20acting%20in%20drivers'%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20probably%20would%20love%20it%20if%20drivers%20only%20worked%20for%20their%20app%20and%20if%20they%20offered%20lowball%20fares%20and%20drivers%20would%20accept%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Feigelson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-gigu-mystro-rideshare-apps-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752744962000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6877f67e85e81483682e22a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-gigu-mystro-rideshare-apps-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Apps%20like%20GigU%2C%20Maxymo%2C%20and%20Mystro%20can%20help%20drivers%20assess%20whether%20a%20prospective%20trip%20is%20worth%20their%20time%20or%20the%20wear%20and%20tear%20on%20their%20vehicles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnewsham%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Newsham%2CAlex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-gigu-mystro-rideshare-apps-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kriti%20Sanon%20confirmed%20for%20'Don%203'%20with%20Ranveer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752744528000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-122630937%2Cimgsize-34622.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fits-official-kriti-sanon-comes-on-board-for-don-3-opposite-ranveer-singh-after-kiara-advanis-exit-the-search-for-villain-continues%2Farticleshow%2F122630906.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F122630906.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EKiara%20Advani's%20pregnancy%20led%20to%20her%20departure%20from%20'Don%203%2C'%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20Kriti%20Sanon%20to%20star%20opposite%