0economy.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20are%20always%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-home-prices-falling-recession-real-estate-job-market-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewatching%20the%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20barometer%20for%20the%20health%20of%20the%20broader%20economy%2C%20and%20some%20see%20trouble%20ahead%20if%20first-time%20buyers%20can't%20start%20climbing%20the%20real%20estate%20ladder.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brutal%20US%20housing%20market%20has%20been%20particularly%20tough%20for%20younger%20people%20who%20typically%20make%20up%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20first-time%20buyers.%20Prices%20soared%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20never%20came%20back%20down%20in%20most%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%20Mortgage%20rates%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20are%20the%20highest%20they've%20been%20in%20over%2020%20years.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20chart%20from%20Torsten%20Slok%2C%20chief%20economist%20of%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-prices-mortgage-rates-first-time-buyers-torsten-slok-apollo-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshowed%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20number%20of%20first-time%20home%20buyers%20has%20fallen%20from%2050%25%20in%202010%20to%20just%2024%25%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Share%20of%20first%20time%20buyers%20since%202010%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6862a1b33d5881a51c1c5a38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221218%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20share%20of%20first-time%20homebuyers%20has%20cratered%20since%202010.%20%3Cp%3ENAR%2FApollo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22201126f9-00f8-4741-83c9-eaeb90ae4973%5C%22%3EGen%20Z's%20shifting%20views%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20still%20being%20young%20overall%2C%20Gen%20Z's%20approach%20to%20the%20housing%20market%20is%20stark%20compared%20to%20older%20generations.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20marks%20in%20their%20lives%20that%20have%20been%20associated%20with%20financial%20situations%20and%20financial%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20Virginia%20Love%2C%20an%20industry%20principal%20at%20Entrat%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Things%20like%20the%20COVID-19%20market%20crash%20and%20the%20volatility%20of%20the%202020s%20so%20far%20have%20made%20the%20generation%20more%20cautious%20around%20major%20life%20decisions%20like%20buying%20a%20house.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20displayed%20similar%20habits%20as%20they%20approached%20homebuying%20age.%20However%2C%20unlike%20Gen%20Z%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20have%20mostly%20embraced%20the%20idea%20of%20owning%20a%20house.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20age%2031%2C%20their%20homeownership%20rate%20lagged%20Gen%20X%20and%20boomers%20by%20just%20over%206%20percentage%20points%2C%26quot%3B%20Odeta%20Kushi%2C%20deputy%20chief%20economist%20at%20First%20American%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20by%20age%2042%2C%20millennials%20essentially%20closed%20that%20gap%2C%20reaching%20a%20homeownership%20rate%20nearly%20identical%20to%20Gen%20X%20at%2066%20percent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z's%20behavior%20suggests%20they%20may%20be%20different%2C%20though.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgo.entrata.com%2Frs%2F223-FOQ-437%2Fimages%2FGenZReport.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Entrata%20found%20that%20three%20out%20of%20four%20Gen%20Zers%20view%20renting%20a%20home%20as%20a%20smarter%20financial%20move%20than%20buying%20one.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20a%20generation%20that%20wants%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20at%20a%20home%20improvement%20store%20on%20a%20Saturday.%20They%20want%20experiences.%20They%20want%20travel%2C%26quot%3B%20Love%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20thesis%20is%20supported%20by%20the%20fact%20that%2083%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20see%20leasing%20a%20home%20as%20a%20way%20to%20%26quot%3Bsave%20for%20life%20experiences%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20invest%20in%20property%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20and%20housing%20experts%20say%20that's%20a%20major%20economic%20shift%20compared%20to%20other%20generations%20who%20were%20taught%20that%20homeownership%20is%20one%20of%20the%20keys%20to%20the%20American%20dream%2C%20and%20it%20threatens%20to%20stall%20one%20of%20the%20economy's%20greatest%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224fb26bcd-01ae-48de-90d0-75009daa78ea%5C%22%3EThe%20ripple%20effects%20of%20fewer%20first-time%20buyers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20housing%20market%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20a%20bellwether%20for%20the%20economy.%20When%20it's%20struggling%2C%20it%20can%20create%20ripple%20effects%20that%20negatively%20impact%20other%20areas.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirst-time%20buyers%20usually%20kick%20off%20the%20whole%20chain%2C%20and%20without%20them%2C%20it's%20harder%20for%20current%20homeowners%20to%20move%20up%20or%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20Kovar%2C%20CEO%20of%2011%20Financial%2C%20told%20BI.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20fewer%20listings%2C%20slower%20construction%2C%20and%20less%20money%20moving%20through%20industries%20tied%20to%20homeownership%20like%20appliances%2C%20insurance%2C%20remodeling%E2%80%94you%20name%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20factors%20could%20impact%20the%20broader%20economy%20in%20the%20near-term.%20As%20Kovac%20noted%2C%20%26quot%3BHousing%20has%20always%20been%20a%20major%20engine%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20so%20when%20a%20whole%20generation%20steps%20back%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20create%20some%20drag.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKushi%20added%20that%20if%20Gen%20Z%20continues%20to%20resist%20homeownership%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20financial%20problems%20for%20them%20down%20the%20road%2C%20as%20they%20are%20depriving%20themselves%20of%20a%20powerful%20wealth-building%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20delaying%20homeownership%20doesn't%20eliminate%20its%20wealth-building%20potential%2C%20it%20does%20compress%20the%20time%20horizon%20over%20which%20individuals%20can%20benefit%2C%20which%20may%20have%20ripple%20effects%20on%20lifetime%20savings%2C%20retirement%20security%2C%20and%20intergenerational%20wealth%20transfer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKovac%20echoed%20that%20view%2C%20highlighting%20the%20historical%20importance%20of%20owning%20property%20as%20a%20common%20foundation%20for%20financial%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20owning%20a%20home%20could%20have%20a%20serious%20ripple%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20past%20generations%2C%20that%20was%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20ways%20to%20build%20equity%20and%20pass%20something%20on.%20Without%20that%2C%20Gen%20Z%20could%20struggle%20to%20build%20lasting%20wealth%2C%20especially%20if%20they're%20stuck%20paying%20rising%20rent%20and%20not%20putting%20money%20toward%20something%20that%20grows.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-time-homebuyer-housing-market-real-estate-gen-z-mortgage-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752743701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6877f75d3d5881a51c1d741f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-time-homebuyer-housing-market-real-estate-gen-z-mortgage-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20housing%20market%20is%20a%20bellwether%20for%20the%20broader%20economy%2C%20and%20a%20key%20group%20of%20buyers%20has%20been%20slowly%20dwindling%20since%202010.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A56%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-time-homebuyer-housing-market-real-estate-gen-z-mortgage-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7